<a class='reflink' href='../4.paois/4.5.pafagais.html#lemmacompatibilityeunitary'>4.5.5</a>

<!-- 4.5.5 -->
<div class='toload lemma'>
	<p><span class='envidentifier'>Lemma 4.5.5
	<span style='font-weight:normal;'>([<span class='ref' data-tag='MR1694900'></span>, Theorem 2.4.6])</span></span>
	<ol class='alphpar'>
		<li>
			An inverse semigroup $S$ with $0$ is $E^*$-unitary if and only if whenever $s,t\in S$ have a non-zero common lower bound then $s$ and $t$ are compatible.
		</li>
		
		<li>
			An inverse semigroup $S$ is $E$-unitary if and only if whenever $s,t\in S$ have a common lower bound then $s$ and $t$ are compatible.
		</li>
	</ol>
	</p>
</div>